Package: disbayes
Title: Bayesian evidence synthesis for chronic disease epidemiology
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: Chris Jackson <chris.jackson@mrc-bsu.cam.ac.uk>
Maintainer: Chris Jackson <chris.jackson@mrc-bsu.cam.ac.uk>
Description: Estimates incidence and case fatality for a chronic disease given partial information.  A three-state continuous-time Markov model is used.  Given data on at least incidence and mortality by year of age, Bayesian inference is used to estimate the posterior distributions of incidence, case fatality, and functions of these such as prevalence. 
